Study by Consumer Reports in the US found 60 per cent of packaged prawns tested contained traces of harmful bacteria . 
  Majority of shrimp come from vast prawn farms in India, Indonesia and Thailand . 
  Researchers found traces of E . 
 coli, MRSA, salmonella and vibrio . 
  Many of the shrimp sold in the UK also come from these farms . 
  Experts said wild shrimp are less likely to contain harmful bacteria and chemicals . 
 